    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>How to Give Away $21.8 Billion</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>T A Clarke letter on Jean Strouse's April 16 article disputes critics opposed to Bill Gates' aid to United Negro College Fund</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bill Gates's $1 billion Millennium Scholarship Program may do more harm than good unless its criteria for awarding college scholarships are altered. Based strictly on ''minority'' preference rather than need, it is bound to exacerbate racial resentment.</p>
        <p>Ernest W. Lefever  Chevy Chase, Md.</p>
      </block>
